&lt;p&gt;Would you like a role where you will be part of a cohesive team, can deliver a high quality service for women and have autonomy? Then we are interested in you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to retirement of a colleague we have a unique opportunity for a highly motivated, ambitious individual to join our team as a Consultant in General Obstetrics and Gynaecology with a special interest in fetal medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interests in gynaecology will be consider in line with the needs of our unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post needs a commitment to Obstetrics and will have a resident on call component, alongside 2 other Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotas will change with the appointment of more resident on call Consultants in future, with the anticipation that there will be less frequent resident sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your life outside HHFT is important and the Trust are happy to consider applications with flexible working patterns that cater to individual requirements; this can be discussed at interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
